
[1]bruise

   BRUISE, v.t. s as z. To crush by beating or pounding with an instrument
   not edged or pointed. When applied to animal flesh or to vegetables, a
   bruise is a contusion that impairs the natural solidity and texture of
   the part, but often without breaking the skin. When applied to minerals
   and similar substances, it signifies to break them, and often to reduce
   them to a coarse powder.

   BRUISE, n. A contusion; a hurt upon the flesh of animals, upon plants
   or other bodies, with a blunt or heavy instrument.
